What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, it was a very interesting course. I think that it could have had a bit more structure, but overall it helped me develop a framework and confidence for attacking numerical problems.

If your looking for a cs elective that is not too much extra work or a survey of commonly used numerical methods take this course! The professor is also very interesting so definitely shop it if unsure!

Lectures are sometimes hard to follow, but you will learn from the programming assignments, which are pretty easy after taking CS 223 with Eisenstat. The class has a very practical focus: if you need to program in real life, I recommend taking it.
